sentences: Eriko Tamura (田村 英里子, Tamura Eriko, born in January 16, 1973 in Ibaraki Prefecture, Japan), sometimes credited only as Eriko, is a Japanese actress and singer.
Tamura grew up in Düsseldorf, Germany and lived there for six years with her family from the age of 8 to the age of 13.
In 2009, Tamura also played a leading role, Mai, the villainess in the 20th Century Fox feature Dragonball Evolution.

Also in 2009, Tamura played Sock's stepsister in season 2 of Reaper.
In 2007, Tamura filed a lawsuit against IMDb for invading her privacy by posting her birthday and full name online.
Her first autobiography, Hollywood Dream (ハリウッド ドリーム, Hariuddo Dorīmu), was published in Japan by Bungeishunjū in 2009.
